      kreXX is already preconfigured, you don't have to cofigure it. But there are always moments when you want to change it. There are 3 levels of configuration:<br /><br />
      <h4>1.) Factory settings</h4>
      The factory settings are hardcoded fallback settings.<br /><br />
      <h4>2.) Configuration file Krexx.ini</h4>
      The configuration file settings are stored in the file Krexx.ini. kreXX shows in it's output footer where it is searching for this file. In Magento this is normally:
      <div style="background-color: #efefef; border: 1px solid #d8d8d8; margin: -1px 0 0; padding: 10px 10px 10px 26px;"><pre><code>app/code/community/Brainworxx/Includekrexx/Block/krexx/Krexx.ini</code></pre></div>
